Tallan Noble Latz (born September 22, 1999) is an American blues rock musician,  who began performing professionally at age 6 and in the following 9 years, he has made recordings, appeared on multiple television shows and festivals and performed with many other blues and other music artists.
That year he played on-stage with performers such as Jackson Browne and Les Paul.
He appeared on The Rachael Ray Show on January 21, 2009.
In 2009, at nine, he collaborated with Louie Zagoras, recording five original songs: "Journey Man", "Slippin Away", "Other World", "Kid in the Region" and a song for Latz's mother called "4U".
At ten he was voted WAMI's 2010 Rising Star Award Winner.

Latz is working on multiple projects during 2013.
In 2008, Latz's father Carl received a letter from the state of Wisconsin banning Latz from performing in club venues, given his young age.
As of 2014, he remained unable to perform in venues that served alcohol.
On July 14, 2009, Latz appeared as a contestant on America's Got Talent.
On July 29 he was eliminated at the start of the episode.
